getPOICloseTo

public java.util.ArrayList<POI> getPOICloseTo(org.osmdroid.util.GeoPoint position,
                                              java.lang.String facility,
                                              int maxResults,
                                              double maxDistance)
Parameters:
position -
facility - a Nominatim facility. Note that Nominatim facility search uses Special Phrases instead of OSM tags. See http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nominatim/Special_Phrases and http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nominatim/Special_Phrases/EN or http://code.google.com/p/osmbonuspack/source/browse/trunk/OSMNavigator/res/values/poi_tags.xml
maxResults - the maximum number of POI returned. Note that in any case, Nominatim will have an absolute maximum of 50.
maxDistance - to the position, in degrees. Note that it is used to build a bounding box around the position, not a circle.
Returns:
the list of POI, null if technical issue.
